rooms.Name: The Gate to Redwall
rooms.Description:
You are before the gate to Redwall, the ground you walk on has beatiful 
freshly cut grass that you can smell as your walking into the Portcullis 
north of you.  As your feet glide through the soft grass and the wind blows
your hair around you try to muster up the courage to enter this Castle.  It
is a beatiful sight, the most beatiful castle that you have ever seen.  You
want to go in, but beware.

rooms.Name: Passed the gate to Redwall on a field
rooms.Description:
You have gone through the portcullis and you see a wide open field, there
is a fresh pond near you, you think of taking a swim in the pond since the
water looks so clean and blue.  Their are little fishes hopping around in 
their. You cannot go in their because you have to get on your way...maybe
just a little swim then?

Exits.Description: Before the Great hall of Redwall
To the south you see a Gate and a road.

rooms.Name: A way around the Castle
rooms.Description:
There is a large castle in the front of you, you start going around in
on a small dirth path.  This path leads you to more dirt and more dirt,
pretty soon you cannot see the bright green grass or smell the fresh scent 
of it anymore.  Where are you going?  Where are you?  Watch out!

Exits.Description: A field to the Castle of Redwall

rooms.Name: A little Pond
rooms.Description:
There is a fresh-water pond here, you already know that though because you
are swimming in it!  It is so refreshing to you, there are fishes jumping 
around in here and having fun.  You feel as if this is taking so long and 
then you get out and get on your way.  Know if only you can find where
you put your cloths?

Exits.Description: A field leading to the Castle of Redwall

rooms.Name: Before the Great Hall of redwall
rooms.Description:
You are surrounded by grass which leads to a large wooden door, there
is metal strips of steel across the door to make it sturdy so you can't 
bash it open. It looks like your going to need the key for this one.

Exits.Description: A field leading to the Castle of Redwall

rooms.Name: Inside the Great Hall of Redwall
rooms.Description:
This is the Great Hall of Redwall, it is an extremely long hall and there
are paintings and tables lining the walls of this hall.  The wall tower
bove you as you look up.  There is a great big table in the center here,
I wonder what its used for?

rooms.Name: Stairs
rooms.Description:
You are at a flight of stairs where it swings around in a chinese staircase
upwards, there is a strange wind coming from the east.  But when you look 
east all you can see is that there is a Tapestry of the great Martin the
warrior. Why don't you go look at it?

rooms.Name: Before the great statue of Martin the Warrior
rooms.Description:
Here stands the great statue of Martin the Warrior, there is an exit to
your north but you see that it is a locked door so then you notice the
key that the Statue has on him.  I am sure you can piece it together from
here.

Exits.Description: The Tapestry of Martin the warrior

rooms.Name: Path around Castle
rooms.Description:
You have wandered around the Castle, for some reason you don't think you
should be here.  You smell rotting corpses and trash.  Where has Redwall
taken you?  Could it be the dungeon but all on the floor is only dirt.
As you turn around to get back to where you once were, you spot a large
metal grate going down.

rooms.Name: In the Darkness
rooms.Description:
You have gone into complete darkness, and your nose burns from the stench
of rotting corpses and decaying of bones.  You try to gain your wits and
by then you realize that someone is breathing next to you.  A sharp
pain appears at your right shoulder.  Watch out your under attack!!!

Exits.Description: A Grate leading into the light

rooms.Name: Dungeon
rooms.Description:
You are standing aimlessly in a dungeon, corpses of used-to-be-players
are here manacled on the wall, until they dared to come into Redwall.
So to make an example they were hung on to Manacles for the rest of their
lives. Or what lives I have allowed them to have.

rooms.Name: Secret room for Martin the Warrior
rooms.Description:
This is the secret of Martin the Warrior, the founder of Redwall.  You
look around the room and notice a treasure chest in the middle.  Maybe 
you should try and open it, then again maybe you shouldn't.

rooms.Name: The first level
rooms.Description:
You have reached the level 1 hallway of Redwall.  Can you pass here
flawlessly or do you have the urge to kill or be killed?  Watch from the 
corner of your eyes and be aware of the doors lining the walls on the way
South.

rooms.Name: Hallway
rooms.Description:
You are in a Hallway and you are getting paranoid from the sounds you are
hearing outside the rooms, you start to wonder if you should enter the 
rooms ling the walls or then again maybe you shouldn't.

rooms.Name: Nursing Room
rooms.Description:
You are in a room with two other creatures, a nurse and a mouse, it looks
as if the Mouse has been hurt and needs medical attention.  You wonder
what to do now, should you stay and help the mouse or should you forget the
mouse and go on?  Your decision.

rooms.Name: Nursing room
rooms.Description:

if the Mouse has been hurt and needs medical attention.  You wonder what
to do now, should you help the mouse, or should you just leave?  Plus you
can always just kill both of them.  Your decision.

hearing outside the rooms, you start to wonder if you should enter the
rooms lining the walls or then again maybe you shouldn't.
Beware of the South's East and West.

rooms.Name: Nursing Room
rooms.Description:
You are in a room that has two creatures in it, a nurse and a mouse, it looks
as if the Mouse has been hurt and needs medical attention.  What should you
do now?  Should you stay and help the mouse?  Should you keep going and not
be bothered by the mouse?  Or should you just kill them both and be on your 
way? Your decision.

rooms.Name: Nursing room
rooms.Description:
You are in a room with two creatures in it, would you like to know what
two creatures are here with you?  A nurse and a Mouse.  It looks as if
the mouse has been been wounded and is in need of medical attention.  You
wonder what to do now?  Should you just leave them here and do nothing to help
them, should you stay here and try to help the Mouse?  Or should you just
kill them and put them both out of misery?  YOu decide.

rooms.Name: End of the Hallway
rooms.Description:
Your now at the end of the hallway.   Didn't I tell you not to come down here?
Well now that your are here you could see that theres nothing to be afraid of.
I was just scaring you!  Well, that was fun.  What to do now?  Go scare
someone else?

rooms.Name: Doctor's Room
rooms.Description:
Here stands the Doctor.  Yes he is in.  He should be in all those rooms
helping the Mice, right?  So whats he doing in here?  Well, maybe he is
on his break, wait maybe he is injecting himself with drugs?  That would
not be cool.  Having a doctor that you need to heal you be using drugs?
Maybe he is waiting for the nurse.

rooms.Name: Nurse's Office
rooms.Description:
HELLO! This is the nurse's office and shower room!  What are you doing in here
you little pervert a nurse screams and slaps you at the same time.  Well in the
corner there is a nurse getting ready to go "visit" the doctor.  Maybe its 
about time you left, the nurse's are getting upset.

rooms.Name: Second Level
rooms.Description:
You are now at the second level, I am surprised you made it here, get ready
for mobs, mobs, and more mobs!  You see 10 doors to your east and west along
the walls on the way North.

rooms.Description: You are in a Hallway and you are getting paranoid from the sounds you are hearing outside the rooms, you start to wonder if you should enter the rooms ling the walls or then again maybe you shouldn't. There are stairs leading up here.  Watch your step!

rooms.Name: House
rooms.Description:
You are in the house of a mouse, it is cozy and warm inside here, you feel 
like you could stay in here till forever!  You want to just go and fall
asleep next to the warm fire.  But if the mouse that is sitting in his
favorite char and wakes up, you better hope he doesn't mind!

rooms.Name: Last set of Stairs
rooms.Description:
This is the 3rd and final level of the castle Redwall, mail Matthias on your 
comments of Redwall.  Did you like it?  There are in fact 5 exits in this one
room alone.  North, East, South, West, and down.  Well, why don't you go find
out whats in them?

rooms.Name: The room of Matthias.
rooms.Description:
This is the room of Matthias, he is standing here watching you and knowing
that you cannot kill him.  You may think you can but if you use a Mage, 
goodbye! Just a little helpful hint for you.

rooms.Name: The room of Cornflower.
rooms.Description:
Cornflower is standing here in the room with a wide smile on her face, I 
wouldn't be caught dead trying to kill her because if you are thats what
you will be, dead!

rooms.Name: The room of Mattimeo.
rooms.Description:
This is the room of Mattimeo, son of Matthias and Cornflower.  He is standing
here showing off his great tunic and you notice that you want the tunic he
is wearing.  Beware for he is but a little child, and a very strong one indeed
for he was raised by the great Matthias!

rooms.Name: Abbot's Room.
rooms.Description:
This is the room for the old Abbot, he is very very old and he can barely stand himself up.  He stays in his room all day and makes important decisions for 
Redwall.

rooms.Name: Matthias' Room of Divineness
rooms.Description:
Yeah Yeah, this is my little room....it sucks...Its never clean..wait thats
my real life room sorry:)  This room is always clean!  Zues aka Jupiter is here
talking to me.  I grab his thunderbolt and kill him because he is so annoying.
Then I get Hera over here and show her Zues body..I pick up his body and 
throw it at Hera, the tbolt sticking out of his back enters her sides killing
her instantly.  What is this room about??  Well I'll tell you, it is a room for
me to concentrate on my "C for Dummies" book!:)  Ok now Hera and Zues are dead
anybody else want to come and annoy me?  I didn't think so.
